====Usage notes====
* As an [[auxiliary verb]], {{term||would}} is followed by the bare infinitive (without {{term|to}}):
*: ''John said he '''would''' have fish for dinner.''
* {{term||Would}} is frequently contracted to {{term|'d}}, especially after a pronoun (as in {{term|I'd}}, {{term|you'd}}, and so on).
* Indicating a wish, {{term||would}} takes a clause in the past subjunctive (irrealis) mood; this clause may or not be introduced with {{term|that}}. Most commonly in modern usage, it is followed by the adverb ''[[rather]]'', as in ''I '''would''' rather that he go now''. A call to a deity or other higher power is sometimes interposed after {{term||would}} and before the subjunctive clause, as in '''''Would''' to God that {{...}}''; see [[Citations:would|the citations page]] for examples.

====Synonyms====
* (''indicating an action in the past that happened repeatedly or commonly''): [[used to]]
* (''used to express a polite request''): [[be so good as to]], [[kindly]], [[please]]

